## Dependencies Between Steps

```
Step 1 (common.js helper) --> Step 2 (brands.html)
Step 1 (common.js helper) --> Step 3 (home.js)
Step 1 (common.js helper) --> Step 4 (search.js, optional)
```

Step 1 must be completed first. Steps 2, 3, and 4 can be done in any order or in parallel.

---

## Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| Runtime performance of `getBrandProductTypes()` over 1132 products x 155 brands | Page load slowdown | Pre-compute a brand-to-category map once in a single pass rather than calling per-brand. The helper can build a cache object on first call. |
| `data.js` is auto-generated; future pipeline re-runs could overwrite manual edits | Changes lost | All fixes are in frontend files (common.js, brands.html, home.js), NOT in data.js. The pipeline does not touch these files. |
| Car brands linking to `search.html?brand=toyota` may show unexpected results | Confusing UX | The search page already supports category filtering via `?cat=auto`. Consider linking car brands to `search.html?brand=toyota&cat=auto` for correct filtered results. |
| The "Other" category in `categoryOrder` has 122 entries | Visual clutter even after fix | Add a "Cars" type group in the brands page that sits alongside "Phones", pulling car brands out of "Other". |

